REQUIRES physics/Eos/EosMain/Gamma

# If FERVENT is omitted, Multispecies is not actually needed.
# Easier to leave as "required", code should still work, but Multispecies will
# contain nothing.
# Note: simulation problem MUST require Multispecies, because ray-tracing unit
# does not have "requires" statement.
REQUIRES Multispecies
REQUESTS physics/sourceTerms/Heat/HeatMain/HeatCool/phenHeat  # for abundM, metal information...

#REQUIRES physics/sourceTerms/SN/SNSBrandom/SNejecta
#REQUIRES physics/sourceTerms/SN/SNSBrandom_test
REQUIRES physics/sourceTerms/SN/Simple

#REQUIRES Particles/ParticlesMapping/NoMap
#REQUIRES Particles/ParticlesMapping/InZone
#REQUIRES Particles/ParticlesInitialization/NParPerZone
#REQUIRES Particles/ParticlesInitialization/NParPerZoneMC
#REQUIRES Particles/ParticlesMain/passive/MonteCarlo/ejectaTracer
#REQUIRES Particles/ParticlesMain/passive/RungeKuttaThermo

#PARTICLETYPE sb INITMETHOD custom MAPMETHOD nomap ADVMETHOD rungekuttastatic
#PARTICLETYPE passive INITMETHOD nparperzonemc MAPMETHOD InZone ADVMETHOD montecarlo

D Bx0       Initial Bx component
D By0       Initial By component
D Bz0       Initial Bz component
D rho       Initial density
D pres      Initial pressure
D gamma     EOS gamma, only for runs without ray trace / ionization

PARAMETER Bx0	REAL 0.00
PARAMETER By0	REAL 0.00
PARAMETER Bz0	REAL 0.00
PARAMETER rho	REAL 1.67e-23
PARAMETER pres	REAL 1.38e-12
PARAMETER gamma	REAL 1.6666666666666667

# For radiation, chemistry
D sim_A_n       Mean nucleon number, neutral medium.
D & If negative, calculated from chemistry data (he_abundM, he_metal)
D & in HeatCool/phenHeat
D sim_A_i       Mean nucleon number, ionized medium.
D & If negative, calculated from chemistry data (he_abundM, he_metal)
D & in HeatCool/phenHeat
D sim_gamma_n   Heat capacity ratio Gamma, neutral medium
D sim_gamma_i   Heat capacity ratio Gamma, ionized medium
D sim_init_Hp   Initial ionization mass fraction stored in IHA_SPEC, IHP_SPEC
D sim_tdust     Initial dust temperature (Kelvin), stored in TDUS_VAR

# average molecular weights, if negative, calculated from chemistry data
PARAMETER sim_A_n      REAL    -1.0
PARAMETER sim_A_i      REAL    -1.0
PARAMETER sim_gamma_n  REAL    1.66667
PARAMETER sim_gamma_i  REAL    1.66667
PARAMETER sim_init_Hp  REAL    1.E-3
PARAMETER sim_tdust    REAL    18.0
